<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFE96A56FA5490781799BD8B" pageId="18" pageNumber="776" type="activity">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFE96A56FA5490781799BD8B" blockId="18.[1448,2656,740,1998]" pageId="18" pageNumber="776">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFE96A56FA5490781893BD70" bold="true" box="[1448,1683,1569,1602]" pageId="18" pageNumber="776">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Shape of Aellen’s Pipistrelle’s call is very steep (near vertical), broadband FM; a call reported from Maroua had peak frequency of 54-7 kHz, minimum frequency of 47-7 kHz, mean frequency of 51-2 kHz, knee frequency of 54-7 kHz, characteristic frequency of 47-7 kHz, and duration of 0-46 milliseconds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
